import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

class AppColors {
  // ✅ Whites (various opacities)
  static const Color white = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);         // #FFFFFF
  static const Color whiteB8 = Color(0xB8FFFFFF);       // #FFFFFFB8
  static const Color white7A = Color(0x7AFFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF7A
  static const Color white52 = Color(0x52FFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF52
  static const Color white29 = Color(0x29FFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF29
  static const Color white05 = Color(0x05FFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF05
  static const Color white0D = Color(0x0DFFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF0D
  static const Color white14 = Color(0x14FFFFFF);       // #FFFFFF14 (border1)
  static const Color whiteBorder2 = Color(0x29FFFFFF);  // #FFFFFF29 (border2 - same as white29)

  // ✅ Dark grays / blacks
  static const Color black10 = Color(0xFF101010);       // #101010
  static const Color black15 = Color(0xFF151515);       // #151515
  static const Color blackE5 = Color(0xE5101010);       // #101010E5
  static const Color blackB2 = Color(0xB2101010);       // #101010B2
  static const Color black80 = Color(0x80101010);       // #10101080

  // ✅ Blues / accents
  static const Color blue9196FF = Color(0xFF9196FF);    // #9196FF
  static const Color blue5961FF = Color(0xFF5961FF);    // #5961FF
}
